    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-01-02T01:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-02T01:30:00-05:00" n="507"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">111.752/1–246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-02T10:00:00+03:30"
                            >January 2, 1946—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 3—12:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Embtel 1176, December 24. I do not wish to permit Soviet authorities in Iran
                    to block travel of US Government officials in any part of country. I intend to
                    continue pressing for pass for Capt. Gagarine and for either Jernegan or
                        Ferguson<note n="60" xml:id="d507fn60">O. Vaughan Ferguson, Jr., Third
                        Secretary and Vice Consul of Embassy in Iran.</note> now that Minor has
                    departed. I am firmly convinced that we should not allow Soviets to construe
                    Minor’s departure as any weakening in our resolve to send properly accredited
                    American officials into any part of Iran at any time. While pressure of work at
                    this office may not permit any of above named officers to make trip, I see no
                    reason why we should not insist Soviets issue the passes we have repeatedly
                    requested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
